sql:
SELECT SUM(ltss_recipients) AS total_ltss_recipients
FROM support_services_data
WHERE region = 'South' AND urban_rural = 'Rural';

SELECT SUM(ltss_recipients) AS total_recipients
FROM support_services_data
WHERE year = 2020;

SELECT family_home, ltss_recipients
FROM support_services_data
WHERE year = 2020 AND region = 'North';

SELECT DISTINCT support_service_type
FROM support_services_data
WHERE region = 'South';

SELECT support_service_type, SUM(ltss_recipients) as total_recipients
FROM support_services_data
GROUP BY support_service_type;

external_knowledge:
- The query implies that recipients are individuals who have received some form of support or aid, in this case, counseling services; 
- Urban areas are typically defined in contrast to rural areas, usually having a higher population density and more developed infrastructure; 
- Counseling services are a form of support that may include psychological, emotional, or social advice and guidance, provided to individuals in need.

- Age groups are categorized as '1-6', '7-15', and '16+';
- LTSS stands for Long-Term Support Services, indicating extended care or assistance;
- Family home arrangements include family homes, own homes, and host or foster family arrangements;
- Urban/rural designations refer to the geographic classification of the service area;
- Support service types can include financial assistance, counseling, housing support, etc.

